3. Data Cleaning

dengue_clean <- dengue_raw %>%
  filter(!is.na(Y_weekly))

4. Rename the municipalities/cities

dengue_clean <- dengue_clean |>
  mutate(muncity_clean = str_replace_all(muncity, "_", " "))

# Rename the Cities
dengue_clean <- dengue_clean %>%
  mutate(muncity_clean = str_replace(muncity_clean, "San Luis AU", "San Luis"),
         muncity_clean = str_replace(muncity_clean, "San Antonio NE", "San Antonio"))

5. Extract year, province, muncity and sum of Dengue cases

cases_summary <- dengue_clean %>%
  group_by(year, province, `muncity_clean`) %>%
  summarise(cases = sum(Y_weekly), .groups = "drop")

6. Get municipal boundaries

# municipalities (admin level 2)
ph_muni <- gadm(country = "PHL", level = 2, path = tempdir())
ph_muni_sf <- st_as_sf(ph_muni)

# Keep only provinces
central_muni <- ph_muni_sf %>%
  filter(NAME_1 %in% c("Aurora", "Bataan", "Bulacan", "Nueva Ecija", "Pampanga", 
                       "Tarlac", "Zambales"))

# Join dengue cases with polygons
central_cases <- central_muni %>%
  left_join(cases_summary,
            by = c("NAME_1" = "province",
                   "NAME_2" = "muncity_clean")) %>%
  filter(!is.na(year))   #drop any NA years here too

7. Map of Central Luzon Region

ggplot(data = central_muni) +
  geom_sf(fill = "lightblue", color = "black") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Map of Central Luzon Region (Region 3)")

Map of Central Luzon Region (Custom colors for each province)

province_colors <- c(

Descriptive Statistics of accumulated number of Dengue cases per year (2009-2023)

summary_data <- cases_summary %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_ = sprintf("%.2f", mean(cases)),
    med_  = sprintf("%.2f", median(cases)),
    sd_   = sprintf("%.2f", sd(cases)),
    min_  = min(cases), # if 0 min use this dengue_clean$Y_weekly
    max_  = max(cases)
  )

9. Trends of Weekly Dengue Cases from 2009-2023

df_summary <- dengue_clean %>%
  group_by(year, week) %>%
  summarise(total_cases = sum(Y_weekly), .groups = "drop")
# Line plot
ggplot(df_summary, aes(x = week, y = total_cases, color = factor(year))) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  labs(
    title = "Average Weekly Case Counts by Year",
    x = "Week of Year",
    y = "Total Cases",
    color = "Year"
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 1:52) +   # show all weeks 152
  theme_minimal()

10. Map of Incidence Ratio (IR) for 10,000 population for Dengue Cases in Central Luzon

Compute the incidence rates using 2020 population

dengue_clean$rate <- with(dengue_clean, Y_weekly/population2020*10^5)

# Aggregate by year
summary_rate <- dengue_clean %>%
  group_by(year, province, `muncity_clean`) %>%
  summarise(cases = sum(rate), .groups = "drop")

# municipalities (admin level 2)
ph_muni <- gadm(country = "PHL", level = 2, path = tempdir())
ph_muni_sf <- st_as_sf(ph_muni)

# Keep only provinces
central_muni <- ph_muni_sf %>%
  filter(NAME_1 %in% c("Aurora", "Bataan", "Bulacan", "Nueva Ecija", "Pampanga", 
                       "Tarlac", "Zambales"))

# Join dengue cases with polygons
central_cases <- central_muni %>%
  left_join(summary_rate,
            by = c("NAME_1" = "province",
                   "NAME_2" = "muncity_clean")) %>%
  filter(!is.na(year))   #drop any NA years here too

# modified color
central_cases <- central_cases %>%
  mutate(
    incidence_cat = cut(
      cases,
      breaks = c(-Inf, 45, 90, 135, 178, Inf),
      labels = c("<45", "4590", "91135", "136178", ">178"),
      right = TRUE
    )
  )

#Choropleth per year (faceted)
ggplot(central_cases) +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = incidence_cat), color = "black", size = 0.2) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c(
      "<45" = "lightblue",
      "4590" = "lightgreen",
      "91135" = "yellow",
      "136178" = "orange",
      ">178" = "red"
    )
  ) +
  facet_wrap(~ year) +
  labs(
    title = "Dengue Cases in Central Luzon per year",
    fill = "Incidence Ratio per 10,000 population"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
